         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Dec 8 /84 ¶ My dear Baron ¶  ¶ If I do not answer a letter at once I do not know when I may! so I break off my work at  ¶ Alternanthera nodiflora ¶  &amp; A sessilis to thank you for your just opened, &amp; r...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">84.12.08a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by M: 'Answ. 5/2/85 FvM'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>Dec 8 /84<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS embossed with crest of Royal Gardens Kew.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Baron</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>If I do not answer a letter at once I do not know when I may! so I break off my work at <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Alternanthera%20nodiflora">Alternanthera nodiflora</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> &amp; A sessilis to thank you for your just opened, &amp; read, of 23/10/84<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M to J. Hooker, 23 October 1884.</p>
               </note> &amp; its most interesting enclosures from Dr Scortechini<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">!</hi>
               </seg> — (What a name for an Italian<seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">!</hi>
               </seg>).<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The words 'Scortechini' and 'Italian' have been underlined and a large exclamation mark pencilled in the margin against this section. In Italian, the verb <seg style="font-style: italic; ">scortecciare</seg> means to strip the bark off!</p>
               </note> — I need hardly say I shall be delighted to see him &amp; give him all assistance here, &amp; shall urge his publishing his new species with all despatch. I shall indeed be only too glad of his help in that way. As to subsidies, that we must attack Sr H. Lowe<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir Hugh Low.</p>
               </note> for — He has returned already I believe.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With your letter came a very interesting one from Consul Sandwich of Crete to whom I had written about the Evergreen Plant that Pliny mentions<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Natural History</seg>, book 12 v. 11: ‘est Gortynae in insula Creta iuxta fintem platanus una insignis utriusque linguae monimentis, numquam folia dimittens’. [There is a single plane-tree at the side of a spring at Gortyn in the island of Crete which is celebrated in records written both in Greek and Latin, as never shedding its leaves.] The Evergreen plane, described in 1908 as the species <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Platanus cretica,</seg> has since also been treated as a variety, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">P. orientalis</seg> var <seg style="font-style: italic; ">cretica.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> &amp; of which he sends me leaves &amp; fruit, the latter differing considerably from the common P. <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">orientalis</hi>
               </seg>.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We are busy at the Herbarium about getting up a Catalogue of Chinese plants by Mr Forbes<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Francis Blackwell Forbes.</p>
               </note> who has spent some years there (not the [Timor land] &amp; N. Guinea man<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Henry Ogg Forbes.</p>
               </note>) — a merchant, &amp; for which we have a small grant from the R.S.<note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Royal Society.</p>
               </note> It will be most useful.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am printing <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Labiatae">Labiatae</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> of Flora B. I.<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3346in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3346in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J. Hooker (1875-97).</p>
               </note> &amp; preparing <name key="Amaranthaceae">Amaranthaceae</name> for press, but I am so distracted with Councils &amp; Committees, official &amp; unofficial, in London, that what with these &amp; Garden work, &amp; my family duties, I am hard pressed to get on.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever most sincerely your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>J D Hooker</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">I have two parcels of plants to thank you for[.] Oliver is busy with them.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Alternanthera%20nodiflora">Alternanthera nodiflora</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Alternanthera%20sessilis%20%C2%AD">Alternanthera sessilis ­</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Amaranthaceae">Amaranthaceae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Labiatae">Labiatae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Platanus%20orientalis%20">Platanus orientalis </name>
            </p>
         </div>
